  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting philosophy and humanities-based knowledge and ethics frameworks in debates and policymaking process.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activity is oriented to include the principles of the Declaration on Ethical Principles related to Climate Change into public policies, spreading and promoting its contents in open forums (CILAC) with the participation of stakeholders, decision makers and MS representatives. 
it also aims to develop activities to stimulate the critical thought at different levels and philosophy education with gender perspective thorough networking and specific celebrations like the World Philosophy Day. 
The activity will also gives responds to the Outcome Document of the WHC in relation to include indigenous views into the History of Humankind through supporting LA researchers groups on 7 indigenous communities and producing one publication.</narrative>
  </description>
